bia Records artists]]\n[[Category:Composers awarded knighthoods]]\n[[Category:EMI Classics and Virgin Classics artists]]\n[[Category:English billionaires]]\n[[Category:English classical composers]]\n[[Category:English male classical composers]]\n[[Category:English male singers]]\n[[Category:English male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:English multi-instrumentalists]]\n[[Category:English people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:English pop singers]]\n[[Category:English tenors]]\n[[Category:English rock bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:Male bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:English rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:English rock pianists]]\n[[Category:English rock singers]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n[[Category:Gershwin Prize recipients]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Grammy Lifetime Achievement Award winners]]\n[[Category:Honorary Members of the Royal Academy of Music]]\n[[Category:Ivor Novello Award winners]]\n[[Category:Kennedy Center honorees]]\n[[Category:Knights Bachelor]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:McCartney family|Paul]]\n[[Category:Members of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:English male guitarists]]\n[[Category:Members of the Order of the Companions of Honour]]\n[[Category:Mercury Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musicians awarded knighthoods]]\n[[Category:Oratorio composers]]\n[[Category:Parlophone artists]]\n[[Category:People educated at Liverpool Institute High School for Boys]]\n[[Category:People from Speke]]\n[[Category:People from St John's Wood]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the Sun of Peru]]\n[[Category:Silver Clef Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Singers awarded knighthoods]]\n[[Category:Singers with a four-octave vocal range]]\n[[Category:The Beatles members]]\n[[Category:The Quarrymen members]]\n[[Category:Transcendental Meditation practitioners]]\n[[Category:Vegetarianism activists]]\n[[Category:Wings (band) members]]\n[[Category:Wolf Prize in Arts laureates]]\n[[Category:20th-century British composers]]\n[[Category:Male pianists]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript| Cleaned up usingAutoEd", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_McCartney"}
{"title_page": "Sarah Hadland", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = \n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1971|05|15}}\n| birth_place        = [[London, England|London]], England\n| height             = {{convert|5|ft|1|in|cm}}\n| years_active       = 1994\u2013present\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = Actress\n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Sarah Hadland''' (born 15 May 1971) is an English actress. She is best known for her role as Stevie Sutton in the [[BBC One]] [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTA]]-nominated comedy television series ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]]'' (2009\u20132015).\n\nHadland appeared as the Ocean Sky receptionist in the 2008 [[James Bond in film|James Bond]] film ''[[Quantum of Solace]]''. Her other movie roles include ''[[Magicians (2007 film)|Magicians]]'' (2007), ''[[Leap Year (2010 film)|Leap Year]]'' (2010) and ''[[Learners]]'' (2007). Hadland appeared in the comedy-drama television series ''[[Moving Wallpaper]]'' (2008\u20132009) as script writer Gillian McGovern, and had roles in the British comedy TV shows ''[[That Mitchell and Webb Look]]' and \u2018Peep Show\u2019 (2008\u20132010), ''[[Horrible Histories (2009 TV series)|Horrible Histories]]'' (2009\u20132010, 2012\u20132013), ''[[The Job Lot]]'' (2013\u20132015) and  ''[[Brotherhood (UK TV series)|Brotherhood]]'' (2015). She appeared in the BBC mini-series ''[[The Moonstone (2016 TV series)|The Moonstone]]'' (2016).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2016/the-moonstone-casting|title=John Thomson and Sarah Hadland to star in BBC One Daytime's new adaptation of mystery adventure classic The Moonstone|publisher=BBC|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nSarah Hadland was born in London and trained in dance from the age of three. During her schooling at [[Wilmslow High School]] in Cheshire, she became involved in [[amateur dramatics]] with Tempo formed by Paul Walsh a now major cabaret producer(formerly known as Scamps) youth group in [[Wilmslow]].<ref name=\"SwinAd\">[http://www.thisiswiltshire.co.uk/archive/2003/11/14/Wiltshire+Archive/7297026.From_cat_litter_to_the_cat_s_whiskers/ From cat litter to the cat's whiskers] Swindon Advertiser \u2013 14 November 2003</ref> Following training at the [[Laine Theatre Arts|Laine Theatre Arts College]] in [[Epsom]], Surrey, she began her theatre career at the age of 19, appearing in musicals such as ''[[Cats (musical)|Cats]]'' and ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]'' in London's [[West End theatre|West End]].<ref>[http://www.wilmslowexpress.co.uk/news/s/513/513379_sarahs_big_break_as_star_of_confetti.html Sarah's big break as star of Confetti] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080409212328/http://www.wilmslowexpress.co.uk/news/s/513/513379_sarahs_big_break_as_star_of_confetti.html |date=9 April 2008 }} Wilmslow Express \u2013 24 May 2006</ref>\n\nAfter six years, she transferred to touring theatre, including performances in ''[[Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?]]''. During this period, she began to develop her talents as a voiceover artist, with credits including the white kitten in the Catsan commercial, squeaking: \"I can't find my litter tray\"; and the America surfer girl in a [[VO5 shampoo]] advert, who says: \"It's great for my body.\"<ref name=\"SwinAd\"/> She provided additional voice work for the [[PlayStation 2]] video game ''[[Dragon Quest VIII]]''.\n\n==Career==\nHadland's television career began with supporting roles in ''[[Bad Girls (TV series)|Bad Girls]]'' and ''[[The Bill]],'' before she moved on to bigger roles in comedies ''[[Green Wing]]'' and ''[[Broken News]]''. She also starred in the films ''[[Confetti (2006 film)|Confetti]]'' and ''[[Magicians (2007 film)|Magicians]]'' alongside comedians [[David Mitchell (comedian)|David Mitchell]] and [[Robert Webb]], and [[BBC One]]'s ''[[Learners]].'' She also played characters for their comedy sketch show  ''[[That Mitchell and Webb Look]]''. In November 2009, Hadland joined [[Miranda Hart]] in the BBC comedy series ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]]'', based upon the [[BBC Radio 2]] series ''Miranda Hart's Joke Shop'' and featuring the same principal actors.\n\nFrom 2007, she has also had a recurring role in the BBC Radio 4 comedy series ''[[Bleak Expectations]]'', a parody of [[Charles Dickens]]' novels and of [[Victoriana]] in general. Hadland provided the voice of Lily (n\u00e9e Bin) Sourquill, the daughter of Sir Philip ('Pip') Bin over the four series to date. She also voiced the characters Ripely Fecund (Pip's third wife, in series 2) and Miss Christmasham (a parody of ''[[Great Expectations]]''' [[Miss Havisham]], in series 3).\n\nIn 2011, Hadland was cast as the new English teacher, Linda Radleigh, in the BBC drama ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]''.\nShe also stars in ''[[Horrible Histories (2009 TV series)|Horrible Histories]]'' on the CBBC channel. From 2013 to 2015, Hadland appeared as Trish in the [[ITV Network|ITV]] sitcom ''[[The Job Lot]]'', set in a busy unemployment bureau in the West Midlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-actor-russell-tovey-star-new-itv-sitcom260412|title=Gay actor Russell Tovey to star in new ITV sitcom|last=Reid-Smith|first=Tris|date=26 April 2012|accessdate=26 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Basil (film)|Basil]]''\n| Windmere House Chambermaid\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''Julie and the Cadillacs''\n| Girl on stage\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Confetti (2006 film)|Confetti]]''\n| Jen\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2007\n| ''[[Magicians (2007 film)|Magicians]]''\n| Carol\n|-\n| ''[[