er\" in Slovakia}}-->\n: {{cite book |last1=Rubinstein |first1=William D.|author-link=William Rubinstein|title=The Myth of Rescue|date=2002|orig-year=1997|publisher=Routledge |location=London and New York |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Segev|first=Tom|author-link=Tom Segev|year=2000|orig-year=1991|title=The Seventh Million|location=New York|publisher=Henry Holt and Company|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |last1=Strzelecki |first1=Andrzej |author-link=|editor1-last=Berenbaum |editor1-first=Michael|editor1-link=Michael Berenbaum |editor2-last=Gutman |editor2-first=Yisrael|editor2-link=Yisrael Gutman |title=Anatomy of the Auschwitz Death Camp |date=1998 |publisher=Indiana University Press |location=Bloomington|ref=harv|chapter=The Plunder of Victims and Their Corpses|pages=246\u2013266}}\n: {{cite book |last=\u015awiebocki|first=Henryk |author-link=Henryk \u015awiebocki |editor-last1=D\u0142ugoborski |editor-first1=Wac\u0142aw |editor-last2=Piper |editor-first2=Franciszek |editor-link2=|title=Auschwitz, 1940\u20131945. Central Issues in the History of the Camp |volume=IV: The Resistance Movement |title-link=Auschwitz 1940\u20131945 |date=2000|publisher=Auschwitz-Birkenau State Museum |location=O\u015bwi\u0119cim |isbn=978-8385047872 |oclc=874233579|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |last1=|first1=|author-link=|editor1-last=\u015awiebocki |editor1-first=Henryk|editor1-link=Henryk \u015awiebocki |title=London has been informed&nbsp;... Reports by Auschwitz Escapees|date=2002 |publisher=Auschwitz-Birkenau State Museum |location=O\u015bwi\u0119cim|isbn=83-88526-20-0 |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |last1=Szab\u00f3 |first1=Zolt\u00e1n Tibori |editor1-last=Braham |editor1-first=Randolph L.|editor2-last=vanden Heuvel|editor2-first=William |title=The Auschwitz Reports and the Holocaust in Hungary |date=2011 |publisher=Columbia University Press|location=New York |pages= |ref=harv |chapter=The Auschwitz Reports: Who Got Them, and When?}}\n: {{cite book |last1=van Pelt |first1=Robert Jan |author-