rvivor of the Holocaust |url=https://www.thecrimson.com/article/1974/5/2/a-survivor-of-the-holocaust-pin/ |work=The Harvard Crimson |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911013345/https://www.thecrimson.com/article/1974/5/2/a-survivor-of-the-holocaust-pin/ |archivedate=11 September 2018 |date=2 May 1974|url-status=live}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Fleming|first=Michael|author-link=Michael Fleming (historian)|date=2014|url=https://academic.oup.com/hgs/article/28/1/31/649765/Allied-Knowledge-of-Auschwitz-A-Further-Challenge|title=Allied Knowledge of Auschwitz: A (Further) Challenge to the 'Elusiveness' Narrative|journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies|volume=28|issue=1|pages=31\u201357|doi=10.1093/hgs/dcu014}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Fleming |first1=Michael |author-link= |title=Geographies of obligation and the dissemination of news of the Holocaust |journal=Holocaust Studies. A Journal of Culture and History |date=26 July 2016 |volume=23 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=59\u201375 |doi=10.1080/17504902.2016.1209834 |url=http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rhos20}}\n* [[Rezs\u0151 Kasztner|Kasztner, Rezs\u0151]] (1946). ''Der Bericht des j\u00fcdischen Rettungskomitees aus Budapest, 1942\u20131945''. Basel: Va'a'dat Ezra Vo-Hazalah. In English: ''The Kasztner Report: The Report of the Budapest Jewish Rescue Committee, 1942\u20131945''. Jerusalem: Yad Vashem. {{oclc|934651095}}\n* [[Ruth Linn|Linn, Ruth]] (13 April 2006). [https://www.theguardian.com/news/2006/apr/13/guardianobituaries.secondworldwar \"Rudolf Vrba\"]. ''The Guardian''.\n* [[Hilary Rose (sociologist)|Rose, Hilary]] and [[Steven Rose|Rose, Steven]] (25 April 2006). [https://www.theguardian.com/news/2006/apr/25/guardianobituaries.mainsection1 \"Letter: Rudolf Vrba\"], ''The Guardian''.\n* Vrba, Rudolf (14 April 2006). [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2006/apr/14/secondworldwar.bookextracts \"The one that got away\"]. ''The Guardian'' (extract from ''I Escaped from Auschwitz'').\n* [[Alfred Wetzler|Wetzler, Alfred]] (as Jo\u017eko L\u00e1nik) (1945). ''Oswiecim, hrobka \u0161tyroch mili\u00f3nov l'ud\u00ed'' (''Auschwitz, the Graveyard of Four Million People''). Ko\u0161ice: Vyd. {{oclc|22143212}} and {{oclc|664734464}}\n* Wetzler, Alfr\u00e9d (as Jozef L\u00e1nik) (1964). ''\u010co Dante nevidel'' (''What Dante did not see''). Bratislava: Osveta. {{oclc|833945571}}\n* Wetzler, Alfr\u00e9d (as Jozef L\u00e1nik); Mehnert, Erich (1964). ''Was Dante nicht sah. Roman.'' Berlin: Verlag der Nation. {{oclc|65468990}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.vrbawetzler.eu/lang_en/ Vrba\u2013Wetzler memorial site].\n* [http://www.fdrlibrary.marist.edu/archives/collections/franklin/index.php?p=collections/findingaid&id=583 \"Rudolf Vrba Papers, 1934\u20132008]. Franklin D. Roosevelt Presidential Library & Museum.\n\n{{The Holocaust}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{featured article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vrba, Rudolf}}\n[[Category:1924 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:Blood for goods]]\n[[Category:Canadian educators]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Slovak-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian pharmacologists]]\n[[Category:Jewish pharmacologists]]\n[[Category:Czechoslovak emigrants to Canada]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Escapees from Auschwitz]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses of the Order of the White Double Cross]]\n[[Category:Holocaust historiography]]\n[[Category:International response during the Holocaust]]\n[[Category:Jewish Canadian writers]]\n[[Category:Jewish escapees from Nazi concentration camps]]\n[[Category:Jewish resistance members during the Holocaust]]\n[[Category:Jewish Canadian scientists]]\n[[Category:Majdanek concentration camp survivors]]\n[[Category:Naturalized citizens of Canada]]\n[[Category:People from Topo\u013e\u010dany]]\n[[Category:Slovak Jews]]\n[[Category:The Holocaust in Slovakia]]\n[[Category:University of British Columbia faculty]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "WP:MOSNICKNAME", 